Text: What we've done so far
In the week before the semester break , we prepared and presented theÂ  5 minute pitch and also met with Jeremiah once just to introduce the team.
The past week we completed the poster and general work to clarify how we needed to attack the project.
The good
Preparation for the 5 minute pitch went well with everyone contributing and also managing to spend some time practising the presentation.
After the pitch it seemed like everyone wanted to have a bit of a break, so we kept in touch a little bit, just enough to see what people are up too.
The poster prep was a bit rushed since we started working on it a few days before the due date, but I feel everyone chipped and worked out well.
The group has a mix of personalities and I hope we are able to get a good rhythm with how we will work together.
There are people who are more willing to wait for others to take action, while others may jump ahead to get things done.
Everyone seems to be excited about the project and Toto especially seems to have taken to it very enthusiastically.
I know most of my teammates quite well so I feel we have good team rapport, which will hopefully continue as the project goes along.
The bad

My only concern so far has been that some people in the team are a bit afraid to step on each others toes, so there have been a few instances of "I don't mind, so you choose" which leads to a stalemate of indecision.
However, this can be resolved if one of us takes charge and helps clarify what people really want to do, as opposed to simply saying they don't mind what they do.
Over the past week things have gotten much better with people stepping up to complete tasks.
Things I could do better.
I have made a more concentrated effort to try to help keep the team organised with everything, but I am worried I have been a little too assertive with this.
Although I am sure it is fine, sometimes I do get concerned that people would prefer to not be bombarded with messages to try organise things.
However, I know that from the previous group, the more people are up to date on what we are doing, the better everyone understands what is going on.
I will need to make sure I don't become too overbearing and make people feel like they have a voice in the team.
I will make sure to take on peoples ideas and let them take charge on things they wish to do.
Goals for next week.
The goals for the upcoming week are to meet up with people in the anatomy department to get better insight for the project and complete basic image segmentation with some UI interactivity.
I'm hoping we can also get more specific with each step we need to do for the project, as there seems to be many directions we can take with the project.
General thoughts

Going into the project there was a little bit of concern working with friends because I was worried we may express frustration more openly with each other, or we may not be as honest to try not to offend one another.
However, I believe that as long as we work hard and try to help each other we will have a positive experience throughout the project.
I've enjoyed working with everyone so far and I'm very optimistic that we can work well as a team.
My goals for the project will be to get more experience on the UI side of things and get a better general understanding of image processing.
Hopefully everything goes well!
Overall
